              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Content-driven funnels work best for small businesses: blog posts drive awareness, lead magnets capture emails, and automated sequences nurture leads. Low upfront cost, high long-term ROI, and does not require paid ad spend to sustain.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How long does it take to build a marketing funnel?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Basic setup takes about one week. Optimisation requires 3-6 months of testing and iteration. Funnels are never truly complete — buyer behaviour changes, and the funnel needs continuous adjustment to maintain performance.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is the marketing funnel dead?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Real buyer journeys are non-linear, but the funnel framework remains the most practical way to organise marketing around customer journey stages. It is a planning tool, not a literal description of how every buyer behaves. Alternatives like the flywheel are complements, not replacements.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
